Debra LaFave, a former schoolteacher, faces accusations of having sex with a 14-year-old student.
She plans to plead insanity to avoid trial.
Prosecutors released photos and tapes as evidence.
LaFave's ex-husband claims she was mentally unstable at the time.
The victim's family wants closure, but media attention remains intense.
LaFave will lose her teaching certificate and must register as a sexual predator.
The case highlights the challenges of reintegrating sex offenders into society.
The media's role in the case raises questions about ethics and impact.
Overall, the situation is complex and emotionally charged.
